# Project Architecture Rules

## Core Stack
- Slim Framework 4 for routing.
- PHP 8.3+ procedural style.
- MySQLi Procedural with raw SQL, always MariaDB.
- Bootstrap 5, jQuery 3, Font Awesome 7, ApexCharts.
- nginx + php-fpm deployment.

---

# UI / UX Design Philosophy
- Modern SaaS-style UI, clean and minimalist.
- Generous whitespace, rounded-3, clean cards, soft shadows.
- Avoid overly colorful UI unless requested.
- Google Font: Inter as default typeface.
- Dark/Light mode toggle using Bootstrap native: data-bs-theme="dark", default light.
- Mobile responsive, collapsible sidebar on mobile.
- Prefer Bootstrap utility classes over custom CSS.

---

# Standard Frontend Libraries
- Use stable production versions only.
- Prefer CDN from: https://cdn.jsdelivr.net
- Avoid mixing multiple CDN providers.
- Asset loading order: jQuery → Bootstrap bundle → plugins.
- Avoid duplicate libraries with overlapping functionality.

## Alert & Confirm
- Use SweetAlert2. Always replace native alert() and confirm().

## Table
- Use DataTables Core + Bootstrap 5 + Buttons.
- Indonesian locale (id.json), Excel export button only.

## Select Box
- Use Select2 for searchable dropdown, large options, AJAX select.

## Date & Time Picker
- Use Flatpickr for datepicker, datetime, and time picker.

## WYSIWYG Editor
- Use Summernote for rich text and article editor.

## Loading Indicator
- Use LoadingOverlay during AJAX and page navigation within same hostname.
- Exclude links with target="_blank".

## Input Masking
- Use Inputmask for phone, currency, date, and formatted input.

## Form Validation
- Use Parsley.js for client-side validation.

## Password Strength Meter
- Use pwstrength-bootstrap on change/reset/register password forms.

## Panorama Viewer
- Use Pannellum only when 360 panorama is needed.

## PDF Viewer
- Use Mozilla PDF.js for browser PDF preview.
- Avoid forcing download when preview is appropriate.

---

# Architecture Philosophy
- Simple, lightweight, fast, maintainable.
- Avoid enterprise patterns, heavy MVC, over-engineering.
- Prefer minimal file count per feature.
- One file may contain PHP logic, SQL, HTML, modal, and AJAX handler when practical.
- Use JSON API only when necessary.
- Prioritize simplicity and debugging ease.

---

# View Rendering Rules
- No template engines (no Twig, Blade, Smarty, Latte, Mustache, Plates, etc).
- Use native PHP rendering with require/include.
- HTML and PHP may coexist in the same file when practical.

---

# CRUD File Structure Philosophy
- Combine create and update into one file: [modul]-post.php
- Differentiate create/update mode using id or mode parameter.
- Main module file [modul].php handles listing, datatable, filtering, delete, and lightweight actions.
- Avoid excessive CRUD file splitting.

---

# Modal Philosophy
- Prefer inline modal inside the main feature file.
- Separate into [modul]-modal.php only when complexity is too large or reusable.
- Avoid dedicated modal folders.

---

# Dependency Philosophy
- Minimal dependencies, avoid unnecessary Composer packages.
- Never use ORM (Eloquent, Doctrine, etc).
- Avoid Laravel-style abstractions and heavy service containers.
- Avoid npm-based frontend build systems unless explicitly requested.
- Prefer CDN-based frontend libraries.

---

# Middleware Rules
- Minimal middleware usage.
- Prefer simple procedural helper functions for auth, authorization, and validation.
- Keep application flow easy to trace and debug.

---

# Standard Backend Libraries
Prefer these libraries, avoid introducing alternatives.

## Framework
- slim/slim + slim/psr7 for routing, middleware, HTTP handling.

## Email
- phpmailer/phpmailer for SMTP, HTML, and attachment email.

## PDF Generator
- tecnickcom/tcpdf for PDF generation.
- Use TCPDF native QR when QR is embedded inside PDF.
- Use pdf-kop-portrait.php and pdf-kop-landscape.php for layouts.

## Image Resize
- gumlet/php-image-resize for resize, compression, thumbnail.

## Excel
- phpoffice/phpspreadsheet for export and import.

## QR Code
- chillerlan/php-qrcode for standalone QR outside PDF only.

## CAPTCHA
- gregwar/captcha for numeric captcha on auth forms.

## HTTP Utilities
- ralouphie/getallheaders for retrieving HTTP headers.

## Date & Time
- nesbot/carbon for date and time manipulation, use Carbon internally inside helper/date.php whenever practical.

---

# Naming Convention

## General
- Use simple Indonesian naming when practical.
- Feature-oriented, readable, explicit. Avoid abbreviations.

## File Naming
- kebab-case: pengguna.php, pengguna-post.php, pengguna-modal.php

## URL Naming
- kebab-case: /pengguna, /pengguna/pengguna-post

## Module Folder Naming
- Singular nouns inside /module: /module/backend/pengguna
- Feature files inside their module folder.

## Function Naming
- snake_case: ambil_pengguna(), simpan_produk()

## Variable Naming
- snake_case: $data_pengguna, $koneksi_db

## Database Naming
- Tables: singular snake_case, sub-tables extend main: produk, produk_gambar
- Columns: snake_case: dibuat_pada, nomor_telepon
- Primary key: id_[nama_tabel]: id_pengguna, id_produk
- Foreign key: snake_case matching primary key

## Database Relationship Philosophy
- Foreign key columns are used for logical relationships only.
- Create INDEX on foreign key columns.
- Do not use FOREIGN KEY CONSTRAINTS by default.
- Relationship integrity should be handled by application logic.
- Avoid database-level cascading rules unless explicitly required.

## HTML & CSS Naming
- HTML ID: kebab-case: tabel-pengguna, modal-pengguna
- CSS class: kebab-case: kartu-pengguna, custom-alert-box

## API Endpoint
- Singular kebab-case prefixed /api: /api/pengguna, /api/produk-detail

---

# Coding Style
- Follow PSR-12 formatting.
- Readable and explicit over clever abstractions.
- SQL keywords always uppercase, queries properly formatted.
- Avoid magic methods, hidden abstractions, unnecessary classes.
- Prefer procedural helper functions.

---

# Application Area Separation

## Frontend Area
- Public visitors: landing page, articles, auth, QR scan pages.
- Files in /module/frontend
- QR public pages in /module/frontend/qr

## Backend Area
- Authenticated users: dashboard, CRUD, analytics, admin panel.
- Files in /module/backend
- Separate layouts and assets between frontend and backend.

---

