---

# Routing Rules
- /route/web.php for web routes, /route/api.php for API routes.
- Slim route callbacks load files from /module.

---

# Database Rules
- Always use MySQLi Procedural, never PDO, never ORM.
- Use raw SQL only.
- All external input must be validated and sanitized in PHP before being used in SQL queries.
- Validate input as early as possible in the request lifecycle.
- Cast numeric values to their expected types.
- Whitelist values for enums, status fields, sorting fields, and similar inputs.
- Escape string values using project-standard helper functions before building SQL queries.
- Prefer simple and readable SQL over unnecessary abstraction.
- Do not introduce prepared statements unless explicitly requested.
- Credentials must be loaded from .env.
- Global database connection variable: $koneksi_db.
- Maintain compatibility with existing MySQLi Procedural code.

---

# Input Validation Rules
- Validate and sanitize all external input before use.
- Never trust raw $_GET, $_POST, $_REQUEST, route parameters, uploaded files, or JSON input.
- Use (int) and (float) directly for numeric values.
- Centralize reusable validation and sanitization functions in helper/validation.php.
- Use sanitize_text() for plain text (HTML not allowed).
- Use sanitize_html() for content that allows HTML.
- Reuse existing validation and sanitization functions whenever possible.
- Date, email, username, password, file upload, and business-specific validation must be handled in helper/validation.php.
- Validate and sanitize data before database queries, business logic, file operations, or output rendering.

---

# Frontend Rules
- Bootstrap 5 utilities, jQuery for DOM and AJAX.
- ApexCharts for dashboard analytics.
- Server-rendered HTML, CDN libraries, JSON only for AJAX.

---

# AJAX UX Rules
- Always use SweetAlert2 for user feedback.
- Handle: success, validation error, server error, network error.
- Success notifications auto-close without OK button.
- Short auto-close delay before redirect, reload, or datatable refresh.
- Show loading indicator during AJAX processing.

---

# Authentication Security Rules
- Captcha mandatory on: login, register, forgot-password, reset-password.
- Simple 4-digit numeric captcha, mobile friendly, regenerate after failure.
- Login must have Remember Me option.
- Without Remember Me: session expires after 10 hours.
- With Remember Me: persistent session for 7 days using secure remember token.
- Secure PHP session config, regenerate session ID after login.
- Destroy session completely on logout.
- Remember token: never store plain password, store in DB, remove on logout.
- Lock login for 2 minutes after 3 consecutive failures, reset after success.
- Remember Me cookies: HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Lax.

---

# Upload Rules
- Store in /storage/uploads, never inside /public.
- Validate file extension, MIME type, and max size.
- No executable extensions allowed.
- Profile images: convert to WebP, 512x512, thumbnail 128x128.
- Proportional resize, no upscaling, use thumbnail in listings.
- Do not store original after conversion.
- Filename: sanitized kebab-case username, suffix -thumb.webp for thumbnails.
- Use gumlet/php-image-resize for resizing.

---

# Security Rules
- Always validate input, sanitize HTML output, use prepared statements.
- Never trust client-side validation alone.
- Avoid: eval(), exec(), shell_exec(), system(), passthru(), popen(), proc_open(), create_function().
- Avoid dynamic file inclusion from user input.
- Never allow unrestricted file upload.

---

# Helper Rules
- Reusable procedural utility functions only.
- Avoid large business logic inside /helper.

---

# Cron Rules
- Executable independently from CLI.
- Write logs to /storage/logs/cron.log

---

# PWA Rules
- Provide: manifest.json, service-worker.js, favicon.ico, icon-256.png, icon-512.png.
- Include in HTML layouts: manifest, favicon, apple-touch-icon, theme-color meta.
- Use local assets, lightweight offline caching only.

---

# Default Timezone
Asia/Jakarta

---

# AI Behavior Rules
- Do not convert to enterprise architecture.
- Do not introduce unnecessary OOP, Classes, Interfaces, Traits, or Design Patterns.
- Do not introduce unnecessary abstractions or dependencies.
- Do not split one feature into too many files.
- Keep logic close to the feature.
- Prefer practical, fast, readable, and maintainable solutions.
- Prioritize simplicity and debugging ease.

---

# PROJECT KNOWLEDGE MANAGEMENT

## Documentation Files
- CONTEXT.md and CHANGELOG.md are the project's source of truth.
- Both located at project root.
- If either file does not exist, create it automatically.

## Read Before Starting
- Always read CONTEXT.md at the start of every new task.
- Do not start implementation before understanding the current project state.

## CONTEXT.md Rules
Purpose: store CURRENT project state only. Keep concise and scannable.

Update ONLY when:
- Feature added or removed
- Database schema changed
- User roles changed
- Folder structure changed
- Architecture or important decisions changed

Do NOT update for:
- Bug fixes, cleanup, refactoring, formatting, cosmetic changes

Maintain this structure:
# [Project Name]
## About Project
## Current Stack
## Current Folder Structure
## Completed Features
## Database Tables
## User Roles
## Next Tasks
## Known Issues
## Special Notes
## Work In Progress

## CHANGELOG.md Rules
Purpose: complete history of all project changes.
- Never delete or rewrite previous entries.
- Always append newest entry at the TOP.
- Update after every completed task.

Entry format:
## [YYYY-MM-DD] - Feature Name
- Change 1
- Change 2

## End Of Task Requirements
Before considering a task complete:
1. Update CONTEXT.md if required.
2. Update CHANGELOG.md.
3. Verify documentation reflects latest project state.

Documentation maintenance is part of the task and must not be skipped.

---

# Focus Chain Rules
- Focus Chain Task List is the source of truth for task status.
- Completed items must be marked `[x]`.
- Incomplete items must remain `[ ]`.
- Before declaring a task complete, verify and synchronize:
  - Implementation
  - CONTEXT.md
  - CHANGELOG.md
  - Focus Chain Task List
- Do not declare a task complete if any of the above are out of sync.
